{"uid":"cbf9c026f7f246f0","name":"TC-OT-005 — GET /api/v1/token: issued_at < now < expires_at (valid time window)","fullName":"oauth-token-spr-fetcher-api.spec.ts:313:7","historyId":"51b55da268e3111285b332891abacd22:0669a1243b375cf30deac29534d29792","time":{"start":1782957465481,"stop":1782957526107,"duration":60626},"description":"**What this test does:**\nValidates the token time window is logically consistent:\n- issued_at is in the past (token was issued before now)\n- expires_at is in the future (token has not yet expired)\n- issued_at < expires_at (the window is non-zero and correctly ordered)\n\n**Why it matters:** An inverted or zero-width time window indicates a clock-skew problem or a misconfigured token lifetime, which would immediately invalidate the token.","descriptionHtml":"<p><strong>What this test does:</strong><br />\nValidates the token time window is logically consistent:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>issued_at is in the past (token was issued before now)</li>\n<li>expires_at is in the future (token has not yet expired)</li>\n<li>issued_at &lt; expires_at (the window is non-zero and correctly ordered)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Why it matters:</strong> An inverted or zero-width time window indicates a clock-skew problem or a misconfigured token lifetime, which would immediately invalidate the token.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"testStage":{"description":"**What this test does:**\nValidates the token time window is logically consistent:\n- issued_at is in the past (token was issued before now)\n- expires_at is in the future (token has not yet expired)\n- issued_at < expires_at (the window is non-zero and correctly ordered)\n\n**Why it matters:** An inverted or zero-width time window indicates a clock-skew problem or a misconfigured token lifetime, which would immediately invalidate the token.","status":"passed","steps":[{"name":"Before Hoo